President Muhammadu Buhari has congratulated former Senate President representing Zone C Constituency of Benue State, David Mark, on his 70thÂ birthday. The president, in a statement by the Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Garba Shehu, felicitated with the family, friends and political associates of the former military officer, who served as a governor, minister and Senate President. The president commended the maturity, stability and focused legislation he instituted during the eight years he served as Senate President and the dutifulness that culminated in the passing of many bills. President Buhari believed the wealth of experience Mark had gathered over the years will be most useful for the development of the country, especially in sustaining peace across the country. He prayed that the almighty God will grant the former Senate President longer life, good health and wisdom to continue serving his people and the country. 